          "date": "2018-01-29 08:14:31.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-10530 utils: Scanning tool for HSM POSIX storage",
        "message": "LU-10530 utils: Scanning tool for HSM POSIX storage\n\nThis tool is design to scan the directory tree of the HSM\nstorage and cleanup the directory tree.\nAlso, since PCC(LU-10092, LU-10499) also use the HSM directory\nstructure, this tool could also be used for PCC to:\n1) scan the whole PCC storage to detach all the cached files\nwhen it is not suitable any more to cache the files on PCC,\ne.g. when a job stops and another job is starting to use PCC.\n2) apply some kind of policy (e.g. based on UID/GID/ProjID, etc)\nfor PCC cache management.\nThese use cases needs full scanning of the HSM storage directory.\n\nSigned-off-by: Qian Yingjin <qian@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: Ife22dc553b89a5e09d7eb7502f46a26782f02580\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
